reviews.text: Overall quite impressed with the dessert here but the only thing that could have been better was the herbal jelly as it tasted like the canned stuff and not freshly made.

An awesome dessert shop (specializing in Taiwanese dessert delicacies) located in an obscure street. The taro balls were neatly handmade by two dedicated chefs. Not only the food was artistically presented, the taro balls were tenderly chewy and lightly sweetened. The sesame seed paste dumplings were equally impressive. Highly recommended!

Delicious, reasonably priced dessert. At half past ten, the store was still crowded with customers both inside and outside the store. The portions were extremely filling and definitely worth the price. Overall a great experience eating at TARONE!
Ordered takeaway and it takes a rather long time for them to make it. I had their taro and sweet potato balls in sweet ginger soup, it’s quite good, but not extraordinary.
Small and cute taiwanese dessert restaurant,  quite busy when we went but they made more space outdoors.

reviews.text:
一大碗芋圓都係38。非常抵食。口感煙韌。
星期五夜晚10點15左右去唔駛排隊。

暫時食過最深刻最好食嘅芋圓，每粒都軟綿，熟得剛剛好。讚！
傳統芋圓有紅豆；芋香味又夠香濃。
大角咀必食。
極高回頭度。
